title: American_Top_40_1988_March_5th
description:
"Keep your feet on the ground, and keep reaching for the stars."

American Top 40 with Casey Kasem aired on radio from July 4, 1970 until August 6, 1988. This is a recording of a rebroadcast from internet radio.

In this broadcast:

A listener wants to know, "In the 1980's, which foreign singer has had the most top 40 hits?"

Casey tells of a week in 1964 when one act had fourteen songs in the hot 100 at the same time.

Casey sings a line from "The Flintstones" theme song.

Michael Jackson is in the top 10 for the 30th time.
